.\n\nTherefore the root cause is localized to the main lamp and its immediate wiring/socket connections in the load module, or the terminals/cables delivering power into that module. Repair should focus on replacing the main lamp and re‑terminating/rewiring its socket and the associated interconnection cables and terminals to eliminate the intermittent series resistance or contact issue that is producing the periodic brief loss of light.'
