n their own right, and because the symptom is periodic/brief and not reflected in the stable behavior of any of the internal circuitry or indicators, an intermittent or poor contact at the ambient‑sensor‑to‑load interconnect (or at the load module input connector it mates to) is now the most consistent remaining explanation.'
