blem local to the layout between the input terminals, series diode, and parallel lamps. In other words, there is no single failing part but a persistent structural issue in how the load circuit is internally connected/represented, which manifests as a periodic apparent lamp extinction driven by solver non‑convergence rather than by any real-time control action or power fluctuation. This explains why substituting individual components throughout the system has had no effect, while the symptom and simulator instability persist identically.'
